title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec KSG
postcontent:
This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

title: For Sale:  Modded Taurus Judge
postcontent:
I've got a Tac'd out Taurus Judge for sale. It was modified by a professional Gunsmith down at Ahlman's guns. They bore the barrel to accept a Thompson Contender choke. 

It is specifically used to improve shot shell patterns. Out of a normal barrel at 20 yrds you're lucky to hit with 1/4 of your shot. The choke installed stops the wad from spinning, resulting in a 80% hit ratio. This means your PDX1 shot or any other .410 will be way more deadly. 

You can unthread the choke and shoot 45 still as well, It has threads wider than the barrel so it wont be gummed up! I was able to hit the center two rings of a 10" target @ 40 feet bench rested. 

The base price of the gun is 450$, the choke threading runs 150$, 85$ Dura coat job and two boxes of ammo 50$ can be your's at the price of 575$ 

Serious offers only. This is a bad ass gun, with Taurus's reliability and lifetime warranty this is a surefire life long gun!

title: For Sale/Trade:  DPMS LR-308/AR-10
postcontent:
You are looking at a DPMS LR-308/AR-10. This rifle is not factory stock and in the 2 years I have owned it I have done quite a bit to it and spent lots of money. I am aware of the recent ban and supply & demand problems, but I am not going to price gouge like a lot of guys and try to get $5000 for a stock POS AR-15. I know what I have spent on the rifle with time and money, and the price I have listed is fair, in my thoughts. There are too many ball breakers on this site, just like Craigslist. If you think you can find a better deal on better rifle, then DO IT. This isn't Burger King. You can't have it your way. Anyway, onto the rifle. Started out life as a 18inch heavy barrel, as listed below.

DPMS LR-308/AR-10
18 inch heavy barrel with 7.62x51 stamped. Not the cheap .308 civilian model. There is a difference.
Forward Assist and Brass Deflector
A2 Flash Hider (Is gone)
Telescoping Stock (Is NOT installed)
Boring...........

Since then....................

Magpul PRS Stock
Timney Competition Trigger at 3.5lbs (Complete Trigger Kit, not junk)
BCM Bolt Carrier Group
Hogue Rubber Grip
Hydraulic Buffer Tube
Troy Claymore Muzzle Brake/Compensator
Burris PEPR Scope Mount (30 mm)
Weaver Tactical 4-20x50, 30mm tube, FFP with external target knobs. Lots of questions on this scope. Go to weavers website and look at #800360. This is from their tactical line up for military and LE. It is not a cheap chinese copy, and is MSRP on their site for $1200.

This entire setup is less than a year old and has seen less than 100 rounds. I have used only Federal GMM 168 BTHP's and my own handloads with Hornady TAP, Nosler Ballistic Tips, and IMR XBR 8208 powder and CCI match primers. There has never been anything besides 168grn and 175grn bullets fired from this. Mostly 168, as I only shot it at really long distances 3 times.

This rifle is extremely accurate and is very reliable. 

Included with sale if right price is met:
A2 Stock for AR10. Had it mounted up, and hated it. Its new.
M4 Stock
Pelican case with cut out for current setup
Blackhawk 3 point tactical sling
(5) Pre-Ban 20 round Magazines
(1) 10 round Magazine

Ammo? I have a lot of my own handloaded 168 TAP, Barnes TTSX, Sierra 175 Matchking, Ballistic Silvertip, etc. Who knows. They were reloaded with the newest and most accurate setup I have seen. I have the new RCBS Chargemaster with scale and power case trimmer.

I won't give this away. I have spent hours tuning and testing it to get it shoot and operate the way it does. Yes, it was a home job. However, I have ALL of the AR required tools and didn't hack anything up. It is done right, and has outshot plenty of built 700's and more expensive LMT and Daniel Defense AR's. Regularly. Attached picture of target is a 3 shot group at 342 yards using my handloaded once fired Fed brass, 168 Sierra Matchking, 43.6 grains of IMR XBR8208 powder, and CCI match primer. Temperature was 47 degrees with a 5 mph crosswind off of a bean bag rest. The rifle is a tackdriver. The scope allows for in the field adjustment for MOA with return to zero. I usually tape a ballistics card to the stock so I have all of the information I need when I need it. I also use military issue Rite in the Rain notebooks. I can provide you with all of the ballistic info you need. The rifle has shot as far as 840 yards at iron man sized silhouettes without a problem. The 175 matchkings work better for that, as the 168's are a little light. The scope has more than enough MOA adjustment to go even farther if need be.

Contact me at 585 322 four two three seven via text or by calling.
